{
  "text": "Models with H, = 100-150 km and q,, = (2-5) x 16' Pa s are roughly consistent with the data at epochs 0-6000yr BP but at earlier epochs discrepancies between models and predictions become increasingly larger, with the observations pointing to lower apparent viscosity values [CITATION_1] (Fig. 10) ",
